        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 17 at 12:16AM EDT until May 17 at 12:45AM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>SVRPBZ

The National Weather Service in Pittsburgh has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Harrison County in east central Ohio...
Jefferson OH County in east central Ohio...
Northwestern Washington County in southwestern Pennsylvania...
Southwestern Beaver County in western Pennsylvania...
Brooke County in northern West Virginia...
Hancock County in northern West Virginia...

* Until 1245 AM EDT.

* At 1216 AM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near
Wintersville, or 7 miles west of Steubenville, moving east at 50
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Weirton, Steubenville, Cadiz, Wellsburg, Avella, Toronto,
Wintersville, Mingo Junction, Follansbee, Wolfdale, Hooverson
Heights, New Cumberland, Burgettstown, Bethany, Hopedale,
Smithfield, Adena, Franklin, Dillonvale and Hickory.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.</instruction>
